#: src/pages/docs/concepts/ResiliencePage.tsx:75
msgid "Each input continuously writes its newest decoded frame into a small per-tile store; the compositor reads the latest complete frame from that store at every output tick and never waits for an input. When a source hiccups, the store simply keeps handing out the most recent frame it has — the \"last good\" one. A brief network blip is therefore invisible: the tile holds a fraction-of-a-second-old picture until fresh frames resume."
