msgstr "Glass-to-glass latency, what each protocol adds, and the trade-offs against robustness."

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/ResiliencePage.tsx:111
msgid "Glitchy, corrupt, and malformed inputs are the expected workload, not an edge case: decode errors on one stream are tolerated and recovered per tile, and a broken track inside a transport (for example a damaged subtitle rendition) is warned about and recovered without killing the streams alongside it."
msgstr "Glitchy, corrupt, and malformed inputs are the expected workload, not an edge case: decode errors on one stream are tolerated and recovered per tile, and a broken track inside a transport (for example a damaged subtitle rendition) is warned about and recovered without killing the streams alongside it."

