msgstr "Multiview"

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/CodecsPage.tsx:131
msgid "Multiview composites the canvas <0>once</0> per tick, encodes it <1>once per rendition</1>, and fans the same encoded packets out to every output that wants that rendition. Serving the wall over HLS, RTSP, and an SRT push at the same codec, resolution, and bitrate costs one encode — not three. A second encode is created only when an output genuinely needs a different codec, resolution, or bitrate."
msgstr "Multiview composites the canvas <0>once</0> per tick, encodes it <1>once per rendition</1>, and fans the same encoded packets out to every output that wants that rendition. Serving the wall over HLS, RTSP, and an SRT push at the same codec, resolution, and bitrate costs one encode — not three. A second encode is created only when an output genuinely needs a different codec, resolution, or bitrate."

#: src/pages/docs/OverviewPage.tsx:35
msgid "Multiview is a hardware-accelerated live video multiview generator. It ingests many live sources, composites them into a templated grid on the GPU, and serves the combined picture as a continuous output stream. It is designed for monitoring walls and production multiviewers where the output must never stall."
msgstr "Multiview is a hardware-accelerated live video multiview generator. It ingests many live sources, composites them into a templated grid on the GPU, and serves the combined picture as a continuous output stream. It is designed for monitoring walls and production multiviewers where the output must never stall."

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/LatencyPage.tsx:127
msgid "Multiview itself never trades the output cadence away: under load it degrades the cheapest tiles first and keeps the program output's timing intact."
msgstr "Multiview itself never trades the output cadence away: under load it degrades the cheapest tiles first and keeps the program output's timing intact."

