msgstr "Multiview Program"

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/ColorPage.tsx:102
msgid "Multiview tone-maps HDR tiles into an SDR canvas (anchored so normal \"reference white\" content stays at a sensible brightness rather than scaling everything down), and only treats a stream as HDR when it is explicitly tagged as such — resolution alone never implies HDR. The canvas itself can also be configured as HDR (PQ or HLG) for monitoring HDR productions."
msgstr "Multiview tone-maps HDR tiles into an SDR canvas (anchored so normal \"reference white\" content stays at a sensible brightness rather than scaling everything down), and only treats a stream as HDR when it is explicitly tagged as such — resolution alone never implies HDR. The canvas itself can also be configured as HDR (PQ or HLG) for monitoring HDR productions."

#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TimingSyncPage.tsx:29
msgid "Multiview's output is paced by exactly one thing: a fixed-cadence internal clock. At every tick — for example every 1/50 s for a 50 fps canvas — it emits one finished frame, forever. Sources never set that pace. Each input writes its newest decoded frame into a per-tile store, and at each tick the compositor <0>samples</0> whatever is freshest there. A source that bursts, stalls, or dies changes only what its own tile shows — never when the next output frame goes out."
msgstr "Multiview's output is paced by exactly one thing: a fixed-cadence internal clock. At every tick — for example every 1/50 s for a 50 fps canvas — it emits one finished frame, forever. Sources never set that pace. Each input writes its newest decoded frame into a per-tile store, and at each tick the compositor <0>samples</0> whatever is freshest there. A source that bursts, stalls, or dies changes only what its own tile shows — never when the next output frame goes out."

#: src/pages/docs/ApiPage.tsx:73
msgid "Mutable resources carry an <0>ETag</0>. Send it back as <1>If-Match</1> on a write; a stale tag is rejected with <2>412 Precondition Failed</2> so two editors never silently clobber each other."
msgstr "Mutable resources carry an <0>ETag</0>. Send it back as <1>If-Match</1> on a write; a stale tag is rejected with <2>412 Precondition Failed</2> so two editors never silently clobber each other."

