#: src/pages/docs/concepts/GlossaryPage.tsx:125
msgid "The low-latency extension of HLS: segments are published in partial chunks and players can request the next part before it is finished, cutting typical delay from 6–30 s to roughly 2–5 s while keeping plain-HTTP delivery and CDN scalability."
msgstr "The low-latency extension of HLS: segments are published in partial chunks and players can request the next part before it is finished, cutting typical delay from 6–30 s to roughly 2–5 s while keeping plain-HTTP delivery and CDN scalability."

