#: src/pages/docs/concepts/CodecsPage.tsx:28
msgid "Transcoding is decoding compressed video back to raw pictures and recompressing it — usually into a different codec, size, or bitrate. Every transcode costs three things: <0>quality</0> (each recompression is a new lossy generation), <1>latency</1> (decoding and re-encoding both buffer frames), and <2>compute</2> (encoding is by far the most expensive step in a video pipeline). Good systems therefore transcode only when they must, and exactly once."
msgstr "Transcoding is decoding compressed video back to raw pictures and recompressing it — usually into a different codec, size, or bitrate. Every transcode costs three things: <0>quality</0> (each recompression is a new lossy generation), <1>latency</1> (decoding and re-encoding both buffer frames), and <2>compute</2> (encoding is by far the most expensive step in a video pipeline). Good systems therefore transcode only when they must, and exactly once."

